&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Staff Engagement Officer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;(Part time 0.6 FTE)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We care. We value people. We are one team. We are Bradford.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We want Bradford Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust to be the best place to work and receive care and treatment and we recognise this relies on our people. Increasing staff engagement and improving staff experience are priorities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting time to join our Organisational Development (OD) team, as we continue our journey to create a culture where creativity and innovation flourish and staff feel motivated and engaged, working as one team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll have excellent interpersonal skills, be able to build relationships and be a creative and innovative thinker. As part of the OD team, you will play a key role in driving and shaping our engagement programme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a job share post, 22.5 hours, days to be agreed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview dates:&lt;/strong&gt; to be confirmed&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you’d like to further discuss this opportunity please contact Debbie Jackson, Organisational Development Manager on 07436 020493.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
